column5: When I went fishing last Saturday my engine died when we were trying to leave to head back to the launch.  Its a 1999 25hp Johnson 2 stroke.  Took 20 minutes of cranking with the battery (can't believe the battery didn't die) before it fired up again.  It has never acted up before.  I called Sandy Cove marine but they don't work on Johnson's, although they did refer me to someone in Stroud.  Unfortunately he can't look at it until next week.  Anyone know someone around Barrie who works on these type of engines?
Not 100% sure, butBrentwood Marine off Tollendale Rd is listed as an OMC/Evinrude dealer, same as Johnson. That's just a little east of Minets Pt.
I use Top Gun marine in Holland Landing area. Fast and good service , give him a call at 905-775-0862.

not Barrie but Leatherdale marine in Orillia ( hwy 11 just past narrows) was great to deal with with  my old 60s evinrude and 80s Force. Quick , good prices to0 . Have also heard good things about Top Gun as well. TB
Thanks for the options guys, will try and check some of these places out.
top gun is a great place but they did move a few years ago  now north of Bradford  .you ca see it on the west side of  county road 11  Top Gun Marine. 2230 14th Line Bradford ON.
